### 8. Body Content Extraction Logic Incomplete - MEDIUM

**File**: `/workspaces/gmail-automation/packages/email-processor/src/gmail/email-fetcher.ts`  
**Lines**: 542-560

**Issue**: Body extraction has gaps:

1. **Overwrites content**: If multiple `text/plain` or `text/html` parts exist, only the last one is kept
2. **No charset handling**: Assumes UTF-8 but emails can use other character sets
3. **No attachment filtering**: Could extract inline images or other binary data as text
4. **Missing multipart/alternative logic**: Doesn't prefer plain text over HTML when both exist

**Recommended Fix**:
```typescript
private extractBodyContent(part: gmail_v1.Schema$MessagePart, email: EmailMessage): void {
  // Only extract if we haven't found content yet (prefer first occurrence)
  const shouldExtractPlain = !email.bodyPlain && part.mimeType === 'text/plain';
  const shouldExtractHtml = !email.bodyHtml && part.mimeType === 'text/html';

  if (part.body?.data && (shouldExtractPlain || shouldExtractHtml)) {
    try {
      // Get charset from Content-Type header
      const charset = this.getCharsetFromContentType(part.mimeType) || 'utf-8';
      const buffer = Buffer.from(part.body.data, 'base64');
      const decodedData = buffer.toString(charset as BufferEncoding);

      if (shouldExtractPlain) {
        email.bodyPlain = decodedData;
      } else if (shouldExtractHtml) {
        email.bodyHtml = decodedData;
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`Failed to decode body part:`, error);
    }
  }

  // Recursively process nested parts
  if (part.parts) {
    for (const subPart of part.parts) {
      this.extractBodyContent(subPart, email);
    }
  }
}
```

